## The short version

Men are practical. If something's broken, we fix it — unless the broken thing is us. Then we wait, minimize, and outwork it, sometimes for years.

Counseling isn't a last resort for men who couldn't handle it themselves. It's a tool — and using the right tool has never been a mark against a man.
